30/04/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Police, in co-operation with the US Drug Enforcement Agency, on Thursday (April 29th) seized more than 8 tonnes of acetic anhydride, a substance used in the production of heroin.
The cutting agent turned up during an operation in Sofia that resulted in two arrests.
This is the most acetic anhydride ever seized on Bulgarian territory.
According to experts, it would be enough to produce around 400kg of heroin.
(24 Chasa, Monitor, bTV, BNR - 29/04/10)
